cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.FL 

This paper deals with the arithmetical complexity of dimension and randomness, which are topics related to computational complexity, discrete structures, logic, information theory, and formal languages. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper involves the use of effective Borel hierarchy, which is a topic related to information theory and formal languages, suggesting the sub-categories cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.FL (Formal Languages) as possible choices as well.
